                <h1>The Inspiring Tale of Rudolph the Red-Nosed Reindeer</h1>
                <p>Rudolph the Red-Nosed Reindeer was created in 1939 by Robert L. May for a Montgomery Ward Christmas booklet. The story follows Rudolph, a young reindeer shunned for his glowing red nose. Rather than being an outcast, he ultimately saves Christmas by guiding Santaâ€™s sleigh through thick fog. This tale teaches acceptance and teamwork.</p>
